import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('year')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data_grouped['year'], data_grouped['people'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of people by year?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    age_counts = data.groupby('age')['people'].sum()
    age_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Number of People')
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of people in the dataset?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    gender_counts = data.groupby('sex')['people'].sum()
    plt.pie(gender_counts, labels=gender_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the gender distribution of people in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
